Date: 13 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNN, 12 Oct 2001 [edited]
<http://www.cnn.com/2001/HEALTH/conditions/10/12/nyc.anthrax/index.html>

Reno case's Malaysia link
-------------------------
The Nevada Division of Emergency Management said Microsoft Licensing
Inc., which handles licensing of Microsoft software, received a letter
that had originally been sent from the company in Reno to Malaysia -- a
country where there are known cells of Osama bin Laden's al Qaeda
terrorist network -- and then was returned to the Reno office.
Nevada Gov. Kenny Guinn told CNN the letter included a check. When it
was returned, it contained the check and pornographic materials, Guinn
said. He said there was no powder in the letter when it was returned,
but that it looked like it had been damp and then dried out. Hunt said
there was no powder or residue on the letter. "We believe that the
person who handled the envelope is at a low risk for infection even if
it turns out to be anthrax," she said.
